The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	New Delhi: Indian Davis Cuppers Somdev Dev Varman and Rohan Bopanna advanced to the doubles quarter finals of different ATP Challenger events following hard-earned wins with their respective partners. Somdev and American partner Ryan Harrison beat Ilija Cuic and Kresimir Ritz 7-6(7-3), 6-2 in the first round of the Zagreb event in Croatia. In the Bordeaux event in France, Bopanna and Pakistani partner Aisam-ul Haq Qureshi beat wild cards Adrian Mannarino and Xavier Pujo 7-6(7-4), 6-2 in the opening round.           
	New Delhi: Narsingh Yadav ensured India were off to a flying start by fetching the countrys first gold medal on the opening day of the Senior Asian Wrestling Championship here Wednesday. Yadav had to overcome Saeed Riahi of Iran for gold in the 74kg freestyle.          
	Pune: Bangalore-based golfer Anirban Lahiri fired a second consecutive five under-65 to open up a seven-stroke lead in the PGTI Players Championship at the Aamby Valley Golf Course on Wednesday. Lahiris two-day tally stood at 14 under 130, ahead of the second-placed duo of Shamim Khan and Rafick Ali Mollah.          
	Raleigh: Trevor Graham, the former coach of disgraced sprinters Marion Jones, Tim Montgomery and Justin Gatlin has filed a $30 million slander lawsuit against the US Anti-Doping Agency (USADA), according to court documents. Graham said in the lawsuit that USADA had slandered him based on allegations that he gave performance-enhancing drugs to the athletes he coached and linked him to the Bay Area Laboratory Co-Operative (BALCO) doping scandal.        
	Rotterdam: Giovanni van Bronckhorst, the Netherlands captain, has decided to bring the curtain down on his playing career after the World Cup finals. I had doubts for months and the decision to quit wasnt easy but now I feel relieved, the 35-year-old defender said Wednesday. Van Bronckhorst will join Feyenoords technical staff after the World Cup finals.        
	London: Gianfranco Zola is planning to sue West Ham United for unfair dismissal after being sacked as manager for an alleged breach of contract, an English daily reported on Wednesday.         
	New Delhi: All-rounder Elton Chigumbura has been named captain of the Zimbabwe cricket team after incumbent Prosper Utseya resigned from the post. Utseya handed over his resignation to Zimbabwe Cricket soon after returning from the World Twenty20 in the West Indies.    
